      • visitCeleraId

        void visitCeleraId(long id)
        Optional GUID of the corresponding id from Celera Assembler. If Celera Assembler was not used, then this method will not get visited.
        Parameters:
        id - the 10-digit GUID generated by the Celera Assembler for this contig.

      • visitComments

        void visitComments(Integer bacId,
                   String comment,
                   String commonName,
                   String assemblyMethod,
                   boolean isCircular)
        Visit the comments that explains where this contig belongs. It is possible for multiple contigs in the assembly to have the same comments.
        Parameters:
        bacId - The bac id (sample id) that this contig belongs. Since the TIGR project database was created projects moved away from being BAC based so even though this id is named "bac id" it usually doesn't refer to a Bacterial Artificial Chromosome, but just a sample id. If this value is null, then there is no bac id for this contig.
        comment - a String describing the chromosome or segment this contig is part of. ; will not be null or empty.
        commonName - A String that explains what this contig is. Often this value includes the part of the comment from and additional ids (for example bac id). May be null which means no comment.
        assemblyMethod - a String explaining the method used to create this contig. This value is often the name and version of the assembler or software program.
        isCircular - is this contig circular.

      • visitCoverageData

        void visitCoverageData(int numberOfReads,
                       float avgCoverage)
        Visit coverage information about this contig.
        Parameters:
        numberOfReads - the number of reads in this contig.
        avgCoverage - the average coverage.

      • visitLastEdited

        void visitLastEdited(String username,
                     Date editDate)
        Visit the info about the last time this contig was edited in the TIGR Project Database.
        Parameters:
        username - the user name who made the last edit.
        editDate - the Date when that edit was made.
